Gunfights Erupt in Beirut Over Investigation Into Port Blast
UNDER FIRE: Fighters from Shiite groups, above, clashed with their right-wing Christian rivals on Thursday in Beirut,
forcing passersby to flee for cover. Tensions over a judicial probe into last year’s deadly port blast sparked the violence.
